Signup for final mission in Lebanon Campaign

Will cover how to conduct military patterns around an aerodrome and the comms that are used.

SESSION:

30-45 mins theory presentation and any questions related to the session and prepping. üìö 

1 - 1.5 hours of practice on the Digital Coalition Air Force server, depending on numbers we may have people go up and practice in groups to make it less stressful <:DCAF:276438258144116736> 

15 mins of debrief and any questions from the session. ‚òëÔ∏è 

F-14s, F-16s, F-18s and Harriers will be available at Andersen AFB, Guam. I strongly recommend that if you don't feel comfortable handling the aircraft that you should get some practice in between now and then. I will explain more in detail on the theory session. The comms can make it overwhelming if you're still learning the air-frame characteristics, I will go through everything you need to know and give you tips and tricks, please bring a notepad and pen for your first few times, I will provide a kneeboard that will help you reference if you're lost at any point.

Key areas that will be tested:

- Straight and level flight
- Flying on speed (on Angle of attack for your aircraft)
- Climbing and descending turns in slow flight
- Landings/touch and GOs
- Using simple radio while flying
- Setting your transponder for your aircraft
- Keeping a good lookout
